1
00:00:10,916 --> 00:00:12,291
[car engine revving]

2
00:00:15,041 --> 00:00:17,041
[car doors opening]

3
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:23,000
♪

4
00:00:27,916 --> 00:00:29,916
[KYOSHI moaning, growling]

5
00:00:35,208 --> 00:00:36,875
[ARATA]
What are kyoshi exactly?

6
00:00:36,958 --> 00:00:38,625
The walking dead.

7
00:00:38,708 --> 00:00:41,500
Theo can give you details
when we get back.

8
00:00:41,583 --> 00:00:43,750
So, there's a way out?
We're not trapped?

9
00:00:43,833 --> 00:00:45,958
[KYOICHI]
Of course not!

10
00:00:46,041 --> 00:00:47,541
-[ARATA] Okay.
-[ANOTHER chuckles]

11
00:00:48,583 --> 00:00:49,708
Come on!

12
00:00:49,791 --> 00:00:51,458
Who put this obnoxious
ritual here?

13
00:00:51,541 --> 00:00:52,708
[AKANE]
Theo?

14
00:00:53,916 --> 00:00:55,125
[THEO]
How's it going?

15
00:00:55,208 --> 00:00:57,208
Hey. We're from Chiyoda Ward.

16
00:00:57,291 --> 00:00:59,708
Senda told us you were in a bind
and might need backup.

17
00:00:59,791 --> 00:01:01,041
[inaudible dialogue]

18
00:01:01,125 --> 00:01:03,083
[FEMALE AGENT]
He sent us as reimbursement

19
00:01:03,166 --> 00:01:04,791
for borrowing your new guy.

20
00:01:04,875 --> 00:01:06,833
[THEO] That sounds like him.
I'm glad you're here.

21
00:01:06,916 --> 00:01:10,083
Is it true?
You found a kyoshi ritual?

22
00:01:10,166 --> 00:01:11,333
Yeah.

23
00:01:11,416 --> 00:01:13,500
We've got stolen
izuna tails in Aichi,

24
00:01:13,583 --> 00:01:15,625
hair from the family god,

25
00:01:15,708 --> 00:01:17,166
some fairy dust,

26
00:01:17,250 --> 00:01:18,625
and mermaid scales.

27
00:01:18,708 --> 00:01:21,041
Oh, yeah, there's also
the centuries-old grave

28
00:01:21,125 --> 00:01:22,958
and some dirt
from Toyama Park.

29
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:24,791
-I knew...
-[ALL gasp]

30
00:01:25,833 --> 00:01:27,625
[THEO] ...right away it was
to create the...

31
00:01:27,708 --> 00:01:29,500
[KYOSHI moaning]

32
00:01:29,583 --> 00:01:30,708
Kyoshi?

33
00:01:30,791 --> 00:01:32,375
-Theo! You're here?
-[THEO] Huh?

34
00:01:32,458 --> 00:01:34,458
[THEO] Kyoichi!
Are you all right?

35
00:01:34,541 --> 00:01:35,833
Yeah, no problem.

36
00:01:35,916 --> 00:01:37,833
[THEO gasps]

37
00:01:37,916 --> 00:01:39,333
There's an Another behind you.

38
00:01:39,416 --> 00:01:40,625
Do you know what it is?

39
00:01:40,708 --> 00:01:42,333
♪

40
00:01:42,416 --> 00:01:44,000
[THEO]
Long black hair.

41
00:01:44,083 --> 00:01:46,791
And the shiny,
golden eyes of a beast.

42
00:01:47,875 --> 00:01:49,791
Is that the thief
we've been looking for?

43
00:01:49,875 --> 00:01:51,375
The one who took Suzuka's hair?

44
00:01:51,458 --> 00:01:54,083
Well, now, isn't this
a strange sight?

45
00:01:54,166 --> 00:01:56,666
How rare it is to see you
with humans, Seimei.

46
00:01:56,750 --> 00:02:00,083
I suppose it has been
a long time, hasn't it?

47
00:02:00,166 --> 00:02:01,208
Things do change.

48
00:02:02,750 --> 00:02:04,166
But enough of that.

49
00:02:04,250 --> 00:02:08,000
I'm ready, Seimei.
For you to entertain me.

50
00:03:45,291 --> 00:03:49,500
♪

51
00:03:49,583 --> 00:03:54,500
[KYOSHI moaning, growling]

52
00:03:59,166 --> 00:04:01,250
[MALE AGENT 1] Not good.
There's so many of them!

53
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:03,125
And we're sure they're kyoshi?

54
00:04:03,208 --> 00:04:05,375
What do you think, Chief?
What should we do?

55
00:04:05,458 --> 00:04:06,958
[FEMALE AGENT]
I'm not sure,

56
00:04:07,041 --> 00:04:08,375
but we've
got to move on this.

57
00:04:08,458 --> 00:04:11,125
Seal off all entrances
to the park.

58
00:04:11,208 --> 00:04:13,208
Keep them in here
no matter what it takes.

59
00:04:13,291 --> 00:04:14,958
What? Are you kidding me? Aah!

60
00:04:15,041 --> 00:04:16,333
[ARATA whimpers]

61
00:04:18,041 --> 00:04:19,291
Be careful!

62
00:04:19,375 --> 00:04:21,208
These monsters will
literally eat you alive.

63
00:04:21,291 --> 00:04:22,208
[ARATA]
Huh?

64
00:04:22,291 --> 00:04:23,875
[THEO grunts]

65
00:04:29,166 --> 00:04:30,541
It didn't work.

66
00:04:30,625 --> 00:04:32,500
-[THEO] Let's go, guys!
-Right!

67
00:04:32,583 --> 00:04:34,083
[ARATA gasping]

68
00:04:37,625 --> 00:04:38,666
Hurry!

69
00:04:42,916 --> 00:04:44,208
[KYOSHI wailing]

70
00:04:44,291 --> 00:04:45,625
[grunting]

71
00:04:48,541 --> 00:04:49,958
Hey! I thought--

72
00:04:50,041 --> 00:04:53,125
[KYOSHI growling, moaning]

73
00:05:04,375 --> 00:05:05,916
-We made it.
-[gasps]

74
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,708
Were you trying to kill me?

75
00:05:07,791 --> 00:05:09,791
I wasn't going
to scream or anything.

76
00:05:09,875 --> 00:05:11,291
The Kyoshi track down humans

77
00:05:11,375 --> 00:05:13,166
by sensing the direction
of their breath.

78
00:05:13,250 --> 00:05:14,666
Ah!

79
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:16,000
That's why you did it.

80
00:05:16,083 --> 00:05:18,250
Can't get a signal down here.

81
00:05:18,333 --> 00:05:20,291
-A barrier?
-Probably.

82
00:05:21,750 --> 00:05:24,791
Why did it have to take so long
for me to figure it out?

83
00:05:24,875 --> 00:05:27,125
So, um, tell me more
about the Kyoshi.

84
00:05:28,125 --> 00:05:29,875
He said they're
the walking dead?

85
00:05:29,958 --> 00:05:32,375
Yes, that's right.
They used to be human corpses.

86
00:05:32,458 --> 00:05:36,291
And what that means for us
is normal people can see them.

87
00:05:36,375 --> 00:05:37,625
They're artificial Anothers.

88
00:05:37,708 --> 00:05:40,083
So, they were created?

89
00:05:40,166 --> 00:05:42,083
[THEO] The difference between
these guys and zombies

90
00:05:42,166 --> 00:05:44,333
is that their bodies
are still intact.

91
00:05:44,416 --> 00:05:46,333
[ARATA] Why would anyone
make something like that?

92
00:05:46,416 --> 00:05:48,083
[THEO] Well, in China,
they used the ritual

93
00:05:48,166 --> 00:05:50,625
to send the recently deceased
away from their village.

94
00:05:50,708 --> 00:05:53,625
They'd wander into the night,
never to be seen again.

95
00:05:53,708 --> 00:05:55,250
[KYOICHI]
Judging by their clothes,

96
00:05:55,333 --> 00:05:57,375
these bodies date back
to World War II.

97
00:05:57,458 --> 00:05:58,750
[THEO]
My guess.

98
00:05:58,833 --> 00:06:00,208
Someone had prepared the ritual

99
00:06:00,291 --> 00:06:01,666
to be used during the War

100
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:04,125
and then abandoned it
when the War ended.

101
00:06:04,208 --> 00:06:06,875
[KYOICHI] So, then, this Another
stole the remaining elements

102
00:06:06,958 --> 00:06:09,458
needed to complete the ritual
using these bodies.

103
00:06:10,666 --> 00:06:12,125
Every time!

104
00:06:12,208 --> 00:06:13,750
When they're about
to lose a war,

105
00:06:13,833 --> 00:06:15,541
countries always turn
to the occult for help,

106
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:16,833
and if it's not instant,

107
00:06:16,916 --> 00:06:18,708
they walk away
and leave dangerous stuff

108
00:06:18,791 --> 00:06:20,666
-just lying around!
-So, um,

109
00:06:20,750 --> 00:06:22,291
how do we protect
ourselves from them?

110
00:06:22,375 --> 00:06:23,583
Well, with sunlight.

111
00:06:23,666 --> 00:06:25,250
[ARATA]
And since that's not an option?

112
00:06:25,333 --> 00:06:27,291
You got a flamethrower
or shotgun?

113
00:06:27,375 --> 00:06:28,541
[ARATA]
You know that I don't!

114
00:06:28,625 --> 00:06:29,916
Why don't you try coming up

115
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,833
with a solution
yourself, Seimei?

116
00:06:31,916 --> 00:06:34,208
-Huh? [screams]
-Why'd he come back?

117
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,208
Stay calm,
he's just toying with us.

118
00:06:38,291 --> 00:06:41,291
Hold on! Why do you keep
calling me that name?

119
00:06:41,375 --> 00:06:44,791
You mean Seimei?
Why? Does it bother you, Seimei?

120
00:06:44,875 --> 00:06:46,708
That's not my name!

121
00:06:46,791 --> 00:06:49,250
I already told you,
I'm not this damn Seimei!

122
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:50,458
He's snapped.

123
00:06:50,541 --> 00:06:51,958
[ANOTHER]
You're not?

124
00:06:52,041 --> 00:06:54,500
You're not Seimei? Is that true?

125
00:06:56,625 --> 00:07:00,708
I see. I was so certain
that I had found him.

126
00:07:00,791 --> 00:07:03,375
But since that's not
the case...

127
00:07:03,458 --> 00:07:05,208
Yeah. I'm so glad
we cleared that up.

128
00:07:05,291 --> 00:07:06,833
[ANOTHER]
...I'll just kill you.

129
00:07:06,916 --> 00:07:09,375
I had prepared all of this
for my friend,

130
00:07:09,458 --> 00:07:12,208
but I suppose
it'll have to go to waste.

131
00:07:12,291 --> 00:07:14,333
I despise how much
you resemble him.

132
00:07:14,416 --> 00:07:15,583
[ARATA whimpers]

133
00:07:15,666 --> 00:07:17,333
[ANOTHER]
You must die.

134
00:07:17,416 --> 00:07:18,833
[ARATA]
Well, shit.

135
00:07:18,916 --> 00:07:20,083
I'm Seimei!

136
00:07:20,166 --> 00:07:22,166
Yep! I was just messin'
with you, buddy!

137
00:07:23,416 --> 00:07:27,333
Do you mean it? I'm so glad.
I've missed playing with you.

138
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:30,708
Wait! What?

139
00:07:31,833 --> 00:07:33,458
Get back, you guys!

140
00:07:33,541 --> 00:07:35,791
They're part human,
so force will work on them!

141
00:07:35,875 --> 00:07:37,958
But it won't get us very far.

142
00:07:38,041 --> 00:07:40,541
-Find the altar!
-What are you talking about?

143
00:07:40,625 --> 00:07:43,250
Do you realize
how many kyoshi are out there?

144
00:07:43,333 --> 00:07:45,833
Keeping that many bodies moving
requires something powerful.

145
00:07:45,916 --> 00:07:49,250
The Chiyoda team above are
calling for reinforcements now,

146
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:51,083
but we've got to find a way
to protect ourselves

147
00:07:51,166 --> 00:07:52,416
while we wait
for them to show up.

148
00:07:52,500 --> 00:07:54,583
-[grunts]
-[KYOSHI moaning]

149
00:07:56,583 --> 00:07:57,875
[ARATA]
Ow! Whoa!

150
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:03,291
[GROUP panting]

151
00:08:03,375 --> 00:08:06,708
Wow. That was very impressive.

152
00:08:09,416 --> 00:08:10,916
[KYOICHI]
What a creepy place.

153
00:08:11,916 --> 00:08:14,541
This must be where they were
doing research on the Kyoshi.

154
00:08:20,916 --> 00:08:24,083
[footfalls]

155
00:08:24,166 --> 00:08:26,958
It looks like the string
is coming from that direction.

156
00:08:27,041 --> 00:08:28,625
-A string?
-Yes.

157
00:08:28,708 --> 00:08:30,666
It's what gives the kyoshi
the ability to move.

158
00:08:30,750 --> 00:08:31,750
Huh?

159
00:08:31,833 --> 00:08:33,708
[THEO] Since their
human bodies

160
00:08:33,791 --> 00:08:35,250
are no longer alive,

161
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:37,333
they shouldn't be
functioning at all.

162
00:08:37,416 --> 00:08:39,708
So, some kind of power
that comes from the altar

163
00:08:39,791 --> 00:08:41,625
helps them move, correct?

164
00:08:41,708 --> 00:08:43,750
That's right.
It's negative energy.

165
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:45,250
Also known as, "Yin."

166
00:08:48,666 --> 00:08:50,250
I see it now.

167
00:08:50,333 --> 00:08:52,375
These threads are connected
to the altar.

168
00:08:52,458 --> 00:08:54,750
They then transfer
Yin energy to the kyoshi.

169
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:56,666
So, we should cut them.

170
00:08:58,083 --> 00:08:58,916
Huh?

171
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,458
You can't.

172
00:09:00,541 --> 00:09:03,541
Not without something enhanced
with a specific magic.

173
00:09:03,625 --> 00:09:04,916
Hey, is that what I think it is?

174
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,208
[THEO] Yes.

175
00:09:06,291 --> 00:09:08,541
It's the stolen hair
from the house god.

176
00:09:08,625 --> 00:09:10,541
So, if we can't cut the threads,

177
00:09:10,625 --> 00:09:12,666
we'll have to stop them
at the source. Right.

178
00:09:12,750 --> 00:09:15,083
Wait, and that's the altar?

179
00:09:15,166 --> 00:09:16,333
There are so many kyoshi.

180
00:09:16,416 --> 00:09:18,166
We'll have to destroy
the whole thing!

181
00:09:18,250 --> 00:09:20,125
Okay. Let's go.

182
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,291
[ANOTHER scoffs]

183
00:09:23,375 --> 00:09:25,083
Do you think
it will be that easy?

184
00:09:26,708 --> 00:09:29,250
Um, what's your
goal here, exactly

185
00:09:29,333 --> 00:09:31,333
-[ANOTHER] Hmm?
-None of this makes sense to me.

186
00:09:31,416 --> 00:09:33,208
I mean, why get us involved?

187
00:09:33,291 --> 00:09:34,666
How are we a part of your plan?

188
00:09:35,750 --> 00:09:37,875
If there was a giant machine
in front of you,

189
00:09:37,958 --> 00:09:40,333
wouldn't you want to switch it
on just to see what it does?

190
00:09:40,416 --> 00:09:42,166
-Huh?
-That's how I feel

191
00:09:42,250 --> 00:09:43,625
when it comes
to surprising someone!

192
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:45,916
I wanted to see
the look on your face!

193
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:48,375
The humans up there would panic
if I were to try it,

194
00:09:48,458 --> 00:09:50,333
but surprises are so much fun!

195
00:09:50,416 --> 00:09:51,958
And that's all this is?

196
00:09:52,041 --> 00:09:53,125
[ANOTHER]
Mm-hmm.

197
00:09:54,125 --> 00:09:57,666
[ARATA] So he's basically
a child pulling a fire alarm.

198
00:09:57,750 --> 00:10:00,541
He's having fun
fulfilling his curiosity.

199
00:10:00,625 --> 00:10:02,500
What kind of Another
is this, anyway?

200
00:10:03,958 --> 00:10:06,333
Come on. Who are you, really?

201
00:10:06,416 --> 00:10:08,958
[ANOTHER]
I'm your friend, Coyote.

202
00:10:09,041 --> 00:10:11,166
I'm glad we've finally
cleared that up.

203
00:10:11,250 --> 00:10:13,708
Back then, you were calling me
a "black fox,"

204
00:10:13,791 --> 00:10:15,875
which I've always thought
was extremely rude.

205
00:10:15,958 --> 00:10:17,250
[whimpering]

206
00:10:17,333 --> 00:10:19,125
[MALE AGENT 1]
I shouldn't even be doing this!

207
00:10:19,208 --> 00:10:20,791
I'm just an admin guy!

208
00:10:20,875 --> 00:10:23,375
Where are the cops?
It's game over, man!

209
00:10:23,458 --> 00:10:25,291
[WOMAN] This could be
an opportunity for you.

210
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:26,916
Weren't you saying recently
that you wanted

211
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,375
a more advanced position?

212
00:10:28,458 --> 00:10:29,916
[MALE AGENT 1]
I was wrong okay!

213
00:10:35,416 --> 00:10:36,958
Okay that's it. We're done!

214
00:10:37,041 --> 00:10:38,875
-[grunts]
-Nice work!

215
00:10:38,958 --> 00:10:40,708
All that's left now
is the Shinjuku entrance.

216
00:10:40,791 --> 00:10:42,875
[MALE AGENT 1] Holy crap!
Do we have to go through them?

217
00:10:45,541 --> 00:10:47,583
[moans]

218
00:10:47,666 --> 00:10:48,875
You see that?

219
00:10:50,375 --> 00:10:51,250
There it is.

220
00:10:53,833 --> 00:10:54,750
[ARATA]
Let's go.

221
00:10:57,708 --> 00:10:58,666
[ALL gasp]

222
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,083
They're young girls.

223
00:11:09,250 --> 00:11:11,625
If the threads are coming from
their mouths, then that means--

224
00:11:11,708 --> 00:11:13,125
[COYOTE]
Surprise!

225
00:11:13,208 --> 00:11:14,416
They're the altar!

226
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:15,916
-You found it!
-Huh?

227
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,791
You said you had
to destroy the altar

228
00:11:17,875 --> 00:11:18,916
to stop the kyoshi.

229
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,416
What are you waiting for?

230
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:22,083
Go ahead and kill them!

231
00:11:23,416 --> 00:11:25,416
So, tell me, Seimei.

232
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:27,833
What are you going to do?

233
00:11:34,833 --> 00:11:35,875
Threads?

234
00:11:35,958 --> 00:11:37,833
That's one way
to control kyoshi.

235
00:11:37,916 --> 00:11:39,541
But I've heard there's several.

236
00:11:39,625 --> 00:11:41,666
♪

237
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:44,625
Those threads supply
Yin energy to their bodies.

238
00:11:44,708 --> 00:11:46,375
So, we just have to cut them.

239
00:11:46,458 --> 00:11:48,500
[WOMAN]
Right, but with what?

240
00:11:49,541 --> 00:11:51,208
This is from Suzu's shrine.

241
00:11:51,291 --> 00:11:53,333
A knife. I think it'll work.

242
00:11:54,875 --> 00:11:56,541
[WOMAN]
All right. Got it.

243
00:11:56,625 --> 00:11:58,166
Get ready to break through!

244
00:11:58,250 --> 00:11:59,666
-Right!
-Huh?

245
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:02,291
♪

246
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:09,291
How did they become the altar?

247
00:12:10,916 --> 00:12:12,083
[KYOICHI] That uniform.

248
00:12:12,166 --> 00:12:13,375
She's from the
Osen Girls' Academy?

249
00:12:13,458 --> 00:12:14,583
[ARATA]
You know them?

250
00:12:14,666 --> 00:12:16,166
[KYOICHI] No,
but they were on a list

251
00:12:16,250 --> 00:12:17,250
of missing people.

252
00:12:18,291 --> 00:12:20,375
Does this mean
he kidnapped them?

253
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:23,583
I'm not the one who took them
from their homes.

254
00:12:23,666 --> 00:12:26,208
The only thing I did
was make the altar.

255
00:12:26,291 --> 00:12:28,416
A friend of a friend
is a soul-hoarding demon.

256
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:32,250
He loves to collect young girls,
so I made him a little bargain.

257
00:12:32,333 --> 00:12:35,750
A demon kidnapped the girls
and gave them to him.

258
00:12:35,833 --> 00:12:37,916
He says they made a trade.

259
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:40,458
That makes sense. It's all
starting to come together.

260
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:44,666
[COYOTE] So, what are you
going to do, Seimei?

261
00:12:44,750 --> 00:12:47,916
If you destroy the altar,
the kyoshi will stop moving.

262
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:50,916
But if you don't kill
these sweet, innocent girls,

263
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:53,583
the kyoshi will continue
killing people out there.

264
00:12:53,666 --> 00:12:54,958
How sad.

265
00:12:55,041 --> 00:12:56,166
And what if they go after you

266
00:12:56,250 --> 00:12:57,916
and your friends next?

267
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:01,083
[scoffs] He's saying whatever
he can to piss me off.

268
00:13:01,166 --> 00:13:02,291
[THEO gasps]

269
00:13:05,875 --> 00:13:07,125
Disgusting!

270
00:13:08,416 --> 00:13:09,875
Shit! There's too many of them!

271
00:13:11,291 --> 00:13:12,583
Stay back!

272
00:13:14,541 --> 00:13:16,166
Kanoichi!

273
00:13:16,250 --> 00:13:18,750
[COYOTE]
Save a few and many will die.

274
00:13:18,833 --> 00:13:21,833
Or save many by killing a few.

275
00:13:21,916 --> 00:13:24,000
Now, what will it be?

276
00:13:24,083 --> 00:13:25,708
You don't have much time left.

277
00:13:25,791 --> 00:13:29,250
[breathing heavily]

278
00:13:30,416 --> 00:13:33,958
Hey! Don't you dare try to play
negotiation games with me!

279
00:13:34,041 --> 00:13:35,291
[COYOTE gasps]

280
00:13:35,375 --> 00:13:37,916
I am not stupid enough
to fall for that!

281
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:40,583
Both options are awful,
and I don't have to pick either!

282
00:13:40,666 --> 00:13:42,666
You're counting on the fact
that most people

283
00:13:42,750 --> 00:13:44,250
would choose
the smaller sacrifice,

284
00:13:44,333 --> 00:13:46,333
which means
it's the wrong answer.

285
00:13:46,416 --> 00:13:49,208
I'm saving the girls
and all my colleagues,

286
00:13:49,291 --> 00:13:50,750
and everyone's going home alive!

287
00:13:50,833 --> 00:13:52,750
Don't try that crap again!

288
00:13:52,833 --> 00:13:54,250
[laughs]

289
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:57,125
I've never seen anyone
threaten an Another before.

290
00:13:57,208 --> 00:13:58,541
Nice. Well said.

291
00:13:59,750 --> 00:14:02,916
Ah! So, that's your answer?

292
00:14:05,250 --> 00:14:07,041
Let me know
if you change your mind.

293
00:14:15,458 --> 00:14:18,083
-Sakaki!
-How are they so strong?

294
00:14:18,166 --> 00:14:20,041
These are teenagers, right?

295
00:14:21,666 --> 00:14:23,625
I'll ask you again, Seimei.

296
00:14:23,708 --> 00:14:26,541
Are you willing to kill
these teenage girls?

297
00:14:26,625 --> 00:14:27,625
-[crashing]
-[gasps]

298
00:14:27,708 --> 00:14:30,708
[KYOSHI moaning, growling]

299
00:14:32,708 --> 00:14:34,708
Or would you rather
let them kill your friends?

300
00:14:34,791 --> 00:14:35,791
Stop it!

301
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:37,375
This has nothing
to do with them!

302
00:14:37,458 --> 00:14:39,625
-Oh?
-If you're trying to upset me,

303
00:14:39,708 --> 00:14:40,875
then just focus on me!

304
00:14:40,958 --> 00:14:42,458
You really want
to see me surprised?

305
00:14:42,541 --> 00:14:43,500
This is what it looks like!

306
00:14:43,583 --> 00:14:45,250
Leave everyone else out of it!

307
00:14:45,333 --> 00:14:46,916
What do you want from me?

308
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:50,916
To be honest with you,

309
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:53,250
I didn't mean for it
to go this far.

310
00:14:53,333 --> 00:14:55,708
It's been a long time
since we've seen each other,

311
00:14:55,791 --> 00:14:57,000
but you're acting
like a stranger

312
00:14:57,083 --> 00:14:58,500
who doesn't even know me.

313
00:14:58,583 --> 00:15:01,000
And you're refusing to say
my name for some reason.

314
00:15:01,083 --> 00:15:02,666
What are you talking about?

315
00:15:02,750 --> 00:15:04,375
So, I guess I just
kept going to see

316
00:15:04,458 --> 00:15:06,458
if anything would
cause you to say it.

317
00:15:06,541 --> 00:15:08,833
Oh! It's the name you gave me.

318
00:15:08,916 --> 00:15:10,750
You're the only one
who called me that.

319
00:15:10,833 --> 00:15:12,291
Please say my name
one more time,

320
00:15:12,375 --> 00:15:14,125
and I'll promise
to save everyone.

321
00:15:15,125 --> 00:15:17,750
What? A-a name?

322
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:19,333
You have got to be kidding me!

323
00:15:20,375 --> 00:15:22,958
[ARATA] He's threatening me
with people's lives?

324
00:15:23,041 --> 00:15:25,125
All for some validation?

325
00:15:25,208 --> 00:15:26,750
He still thinks I'm Seimei.

326
00:15:26,833 --> 00:15:28,250
[KYOICHI]
M-Miyako!

327
00:15:29,333 --> 00:15:30,958
[ARATA]
Sakaki! Theo!

328
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:36,666
What is his name? Think!

329
00:15:36,750 --> 00:15:38,791
-[growling]
-[AKANE gasps]

330
00:15:38,875 --> 00:15:40,500
Akane, no!

331
00:15:40,583 --> 00:15:41,833
[gunshot]

332
00:15:41,916 --> 00:15:42,750
[BOTH gasp]

333
00:15:43,791 --> 00:15:45,750
Looks like we made it here
just in time!

334
00:15:51,125 --> 00:15:52,541
[MALE AGENT 3]
Everyone get back!

335
00:15:55,291 --> 00:15:58,208
[moaning]

336
00:15:58,291 --> 00:16:00,083
[steam hissing]

337
00:16:00,166 --> 00:16:01,125
Are you okay?

338
00:16:01,208 --> 00:16:02,875
We heard
Shinjuku needed backup

339
00:16:02,958 --> 00:16:04,333
and rushed over.

340
00:16:04,416 --> 00:16:07,125
[sirens wailing]

341
00:16:14,791 --> 00:16:17,916
[moaning]

342
00:16:20,875 --> 00:16:22,083
It's not stopping them?

343
00:16:29,708 --> 00:16:31,000
The only way
we're gonna end this

344
00:16:31,083 --> 00:16:32,500
is to cut off their life source.

345
00:16:32,583 --> 00:16:33,875
Do you know where that would be?

346
00:16:33,958 --> 00:16:35,833
Underground, probably.

347
00:16:35,916 --> 00:16:38,750
I think the Shinjuku guys
were on their way down there.

348
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:40,625
But I haven't heard
from them in a while.

349
00:16:42,333 --> 00:16:44,625
[ARATA] Come on, think.
What could it be?

350
00:16:44,708 --> 00:16:47,166
[COYOTE]
I'm your friend, Coyote.

351
00:16:47,250 --> 00:16:49,791
Back then you were calling me
a "black fox,"

352
00:16:49,875 --> 00:16:52,291
which I've always thought
was extremely rude.

353
00:16:52,375 --> 00:16:54,583
[ARATA] Didn't Grandpa say
something about that?

354
00:16:54,666 --> 00:16:56,916
Seimei and black fox
sound familiar.

355
00:16:58,416 --> 00:17:00,000
[YOUNG ARATA]
A yokai?

356
00:17:00,083 --> 00:17:02,625
Yes, that's right.
Seimei commanded them.

357
00:17:02,708 --> 00:17:05,500
He commanded many yokai
when he was still around.

358
00:17:08,166 --> 00:17:09,541
I remember.

359
00:17:09,625 --> 00:17:10,791
Okay.

360
00:17:10,875 --> 00:17:13,125
It was just a story.

361
00:17:13,208 --> 00:17:14,791
Seimei named his yokai friend

362
00:17:14,875 --> 00:17:16,666
and refused to treat him
like a servant.

363
00:17:17,666 --> 00:17:19,583
He named him after
a black fox he knew

364
00:17:19,666 --> 00:17:21,541
who had deep, golden eyes.

365
00:17:21,625 --> 00:17:23,041
The name was...

366
00:17:23,125 --> 00:17:24,291
Kohaku!

367
00:17:24,375 --> 00:17:25,958
[COYOTE gasps]

368
00:17:38,625 --> 00:17:42,291
♪

369
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:45,875
A-ha! Thank you, Seimei!

370
00:17:45,958 --> 00:17:47,708
Thank you for saying my name!

371
00:17:47,791 --> 00:17:49,416
The one you picked out
just for me!

372
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:50,666
Huh?

373
00:17:50,750 --> 00:17:53,625
♪

374
00:17:53,708 --> 00:17:54,583
[KYOICHI groans]

375
00:17:55,583 --> 00:17:56,708
[KYOICHI]
Is it over?

376
00:17:58,583 --> 00:18:00,041
[MALE AGENT 1]
What's happening to them?

377
00:18:00,125 --> 00:18:02,625
Someone must have found a way
to stop the Yin energy.

378
00:18:04,458 --> 00:18:07,125
And we're still alive.
That's quite a relief.

379
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:11,708
[SENDA]
Good job!

380
00:18:11,791 --> 00:18:14,708
Best part is everyone survived.

381
00:18:14,791 --> 00:18:16,583
Extra special thanks
to Chiyoda Ward

382
00:18:16,666 --> 00:18:18,500
for jumping in to help.

383
00:18:18,583 --> 00:18:20,000
It was nothing.

384
00:18:20,083 --> 00:18:22,458
You didn't have to bust out
the police helicopter.

385
00:18:22,541 --> 00:18:25,333
I may not have power,
but I do have connections.

386
00:18:25,416 --> 00:18:28,166
We're so grateful for your help
in getting Suzuka's hair back.

387
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:29,958
We couldn't have done it
without you.

388
00:18:30,041 --> 00:18:31,500
Thank you very much.

389
00:18:32,666 --> 00:18:35,166
But this means we're even
for the use of Miyako's skills.

390
00:18:36,750 --> 00:18:38,125
[WOMAN] All right,
let's get out of here.

391
00:18:38,208 --> 00:18:40,625
Hey! Don't run off so fast!

392
00:18:40,708 --> 00:18:41,666
[chuckles awkwardly]

393
00:18:43,250 --> 00:18:45,125
Well, looks like
we managed to keep it

394
00:18:45,208 --> 00:18:47,000
from getting out of hand
for the most part.

395
00:18:47,083 --> 00:18:48,541
Thank you, sir.

396
00:18:49,958 --> 00:18:51,083
How do you know him?

397
00:18:51,166 --> 00:18:52,833
[THEO]
He's a detective specializing

398
00:18:52,916 --> 00:18:54,041
in Another incidents.

399
00:18:54,125 --> 00:18:55,375
I heard you even found

400
00:18:55,458 --> 00:18:57,583
the missing
high school girls down there.

401
00:18:57,666 --> 00:19:00,416
Those Anothers, am I right?
Always up to no good.

402
00:19:00,500 --> 00:19:01,916
Oh, by the way,

403
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:04,375
I'm free to handle the report
for this on my own,

404
00:19:04,458 --> 00:19:06,125
if that's all right with you.

405
00:19:06,208 --> 00:19:07,750
That's more than all right.

406
00:19:07,833 --> 00:19:10,000
I'm pretty sure "four missing
high school girls

407
00:19:10,083 --> 00:19:12,416
discovered in a creepy facility
from World War II"

408
00:19:12,500 --> 00:19:13,833
is out of my wheelhouse.

409
00:19:13,916 --> 00:19:16,166
And probably more than
any government employee

410
00:19:16,250 --> 00:19:17,458
should handle.

411
00:19:17,541 --> 00:19:19,000
Stop brown-nosing me.

412
00:19:19,083 --> 00:19:20,958
Can I at least count on you
to help me put together

413
00:19:21,041 --> 00:19:22,416
a convincing story?

414
00:19:22,500 --> 00:19:23,958
I don't see why not.

415
00:19:24,041 --> 00:19:25,791
-[MALE AGENT 2] Yokoyama, sir?
-What is it?

416
00:19:25,875 --> 00:19:27,416
We finished making the calls.

417
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:28,625
The girls are safe.

418
00:19:28,708 --> 00:19:30,916
They were picked up
in an ambulance.

419
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,291
[YOKOYAMA]
Good job.

420
00:19:32,375 --> 00:19:33,708
Now we just have
to come up

421
00:19:33,791 --> 00:19:35,333
with a way to explain this.

422
00:19:35,416 --> 00:19:38,541
I guess we could always say
there was another gas leak.

423
00:19:38,625 --> 00:19:40,125
But you just used that.

424
00:19:40,208 --> 00:19:41,541
[YOKOYAMA]
Unexploded shell, then?

425
00:19:41,625 --> 00:19:43,041
[MALE AGENT 2]
The Ichigaya crew will make

426
00:19:43,125 --> 00:19:44,333
another complaint.

427
00:19:44,416 --> 00:19:47,083
A detective specializing
in Anothers?

428
00:19:47,166 --> 00:19:48,541
That's pretty cool.

429
00:19:48,625 --> 00:19:51,041
[KYOICHI] It's better in theory
than in practice.

430
00:19:51,125 --> 00:19:53,333
It's not like they can arrest
invisible Anothers

431
00:19:53,416 --> 00:19:56,291
or put them on trial
or anything like that.

432
00:19:56,375 --> 00:19:58,875
Mainly, their job is coming up
with a plausible story

433
00:19:58,958 --> 00:20:00,750
that the victims
can understand.

434
00:20:00,833 --> 00:20:03,000
More like offering
peace of mind.

435
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,583
Yeah. That's helpful.

436
00:20:05,666 --> 00:20:07,375
Oh, hey, Arata.

437
00:20:07,458 --> 00:20:09,333
I'm sure we're all dying
to know here.

438
00:20:09,416 --> 00:20:12,458
What is that thing that's
floating behind you right now?

439
00:20:12,541 --> 00:20:14,083
Oh, well.

440
00:20:14,166 --> 00:20:16,250
He's the one who stole
all those missing items.

441
00:20:16,333 --> 00:20:18,416
Seimei's friend, apparently.

442
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:19,958
He goes by Coyote, I think.

443
00:20:20,041 --> 00:20:21,500
[SENDA]
You think?

444
00:20:21,583 --> 00:20:24,000
Do I need
to introduce myself formally?

445
00:20:24,083 --> 00:20:26,208
Because to be honest,
I'm not interested

446
00:20:26,291 --> 00:20:29,416
in being called any other name
than the one you gave me.

447
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:31,083
However, most people
who are privileged

448
00:20:31,166 --> 00:20:33,416
to serve me call me this:

449
00:20:34,666 --> 00:20:36,166
Huehuecóyotl.

450
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:37,916
Pleased to make
your acquaintance.

451
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:40,125
So... that's what
he just said.

452
00:20:40,208 --> 00:20:41,750
Huehuecóyotl?

453
00:20:41,833 --> 00:20:42,791
Huh?

454
00:20:45,916 --> 00:20:47,875
[THEO]
Huehuecóyotl.

455
00:20:47,958 --> 00:20:51,708
He was the god of music
and dance in the Aztec religion.

456
00:20:51,791 --> 00:20:54,875
But he was also known
as a great trickster god,

457
00:20:54,958 --> 00:20:57,500
causing fights between man
and their gods.

458
00:20:57,583 --> 00:21:01,125
He created chaos and sowed seeds
of murder for his own amusement.

459
00:21:01,208 --> 00:21:03,250
[ARATA]
Are you sure he was a god?

460
00:21:03,333 --> 00:21:05,750
[THEO]
Yes! God of disaster!

461
00:21:05,833 --> 00:21:07,458
If something like that
is haunting you,

462
00:21:07,541 --> 00:21:09,875
you could be exiled
from this country!

463
00:21:09,958 --> 00:21:11,250
Well, that's rather rude.

464
00:21:11,333 --> 00:21:12,833
And I'm not some
murder connoisseur.

465
00:21:12,916 --> 00:21:14,125
I dabble occasionally.

466
00:21:15,583 --> 00:21:16,583
[ARATA]
Get off me!

467
00:21:17,583 --> 00:21:18,958
How fascinating.

468
00:21:19,041 --> 00:21:20,833
Being chosen by a chaos god.

469
00:21:20,916 --> 00:21:23,166
-[ARATA shouting, indistinct]
-You okay?

470
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:25,833
He told us how he found
the missing girls.

471
00:21:25,916 --> 00:21:28,708
He said he made a trade
with a demon.

472
00:21:28,791 --> 00:21:29,625
A friend of his.

473
00:21:30,625 --> 00:21:32,583
It's been over ten years now,

474
00:21:32,666 --> 00:21:35,125
but I finally have a clue
about my sister.

475
00:21:35,208 --> 00:21:36,625
As to where
she could possibly be.

476
00:21:36,708 --> 00:21:38,333
I said get off of me!

477
00:21:38,416 --> 00:21:40,000
I'm serious,
leave me alone!

478
00:21:40,083 --> 00:21:43,208
Aw, you don't have
to be so cold, Seimei!

479
00:21:44,208 --> 00:21:47,458
Yeah, about that.
My name is Arata Miyako!

480
00:21:47,541 --> 00:21:49,375
Quit calling me Seimei!

481
00:21:49,458 --> 00:21:53,000
♪

482
00:21:53,083 --> 00:21:55,541
My name is Abe no Seimei.

483
00:21:55,625 --> 00:21:57,833
You may only call me Seimei.

484
00:21:57,916 --> 00:21:59,833
-Do you understand?
-Do you understand, Kohaku?

485
00:22:03,041 --> 00:22:06,000
Yup! I got it! Arata!

